WEBVTT

00:00.467 --> 00:01.600
We've got to do something
     about Pope.

00:01.601 --> 00:02.801
 He charged a cop --
just pulled out his gun

00:02.803 --> 00:04.136
     and headed
  straight for him.

00:04.138 --> 00:06.138
We've got to do something,
or somebody's gonna end up dead.

00:06.140 --> 00:07.939
               I'll be in town
                 for a bit.

00:07.942 --> 00:09.874
         There is a lot of money
                on the table.

00:09.876 --> 00:11.009
 What does he want?

00:11.011 --> 00:13.345
               A sculpture --
      800K if we get it for him.

00:13.347 --> 00:15.547
 She got a new job.
Might need all of us.

00:15.549 --> 00:17.482
        Smurf's not gonna
           like that.

00:17.484 --> 00:21.019
 Let's just say that
you did kill Morgan.

00:21.021 --> 00:24.022
 You stick with me.

00:24.024 --> 00:25.624
      We need a new lawyer.

00:25.626 --> 00:26.825
              Pope:
      You remember Angela.

00:26.827 --> 00:29.561
        I said she could
         crash with us.

00:29.563 --> 00:31.496
      That's very generous
             of you.

00:31.498 --> 00:32.831
 Colin: We've got to
   ditch the car.

00:32.833 --> 00:33.732
      Hurry up.

00:35.000 --> 00:41.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:43.377 --> 00:49.181
      ♪ She stares deeply ♪

00:49.183 --> 00:53.051
      ♪ Locked inside me ♪

00:53.053 --> 00:59.123
      ♪ Burnin' brightly ♪

00:59.125 --> 01:04.929
      ♪ One they know that
         I cannot take ♪

01:04.931 --> 01:08.333
      ♪ Waitin' for it all
           to begin ♪

01:08.335 --> 01:10.935
       ♪ Every night, now,
          they'll win ♪

01:10.937 --> 01:15.607
                     ♪♪

01:15.609 --> 01:18.076
         ♪ Come and meet
         my black hole ♪

01:18.078 --> 01:21.814
    ♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:21.816 --> 01:25.684
     ♪ Got a big black hole

01:25.686 --> 01:29.488
        ♪ I've got a big
          black hole ♪

01:29.490 --> 01:33.692
     ♪ I've got a big black,
        big black hole ♪

01:33.694 --> 01:37.830
     ♪ Got a big black hole
         inside of me ♪

01:40.634 --> 01:46.405
          [ Music plays
        in the distance ]

01:56.851 --> 01:59.718
 Damn, I can barely
   remember that.

01:59.720 --> 02:01.253
        Manny: Hey, guys.
         Try a brownie.

02:01.255 --> 02:03.988
     Absolutely.
       Please.

02:03.990 --> 02:05.457
Just like old times.

02:05.459 --> 02:08.259
     Janine, have a brownie.

02:08.262 --> 02:09.862
            Careful.

02:09.864 --> 02:11.930
      Don't worry about me.

02:11.932 --> 02:13.666
              -Two?
             -Whoa.

02:13.668 --> 02:15.868
Have you had Manny's
secret recipe before?

02:15.870 --> 02:18.203
     -It's not that secret.
           -All right.

02:18.205 --> 02:20.939
In two hours, you'll be
staring at the wall, drooling.

02:20.941 --> 02:22.274
           We'll see.

02:22.276 --> 02:25.677
Cops bust in here, I ain't
carrying all your asses out.

02:25.679 --> 02:27.079
              Lou:
        Would you relax?

02:27.081 --> 02:31.083
 If the cops knew where we were,
  they'd have been here by now.

02:31.085 --> 02:33.017
        Enjoy the party.

02:33.019 --> 02:33.986
           Chill out.

02:52.706 --> 02:57.643
    [ Music plays, muffled ]

03:01.848 --> 03:05.384
       [ Music continues ]

03:07.788 --> 03:08.787
         [ Music stops ]

03:08.789 --> 03:10.722
           This won't take long,
                  Ms. Cody.

03:10.724 --> 03:14.126
         Turn the music
            back on.

03:14.128 --> 03:17.496
        [ Music resumes ]

03:19.400 --> 03:24.869
                     ♪♪

03:24.871 --> 03:26.939
  Frankie: The walls and doors
        are mostly glass.

03:26.941 --> 03:28.941
     Two security guards --
           rent-a-cops

03:28.943 --> 03:31.610
    to clear homeless people
         off the steps.

03:31.612 --> 03:34.413
       Cameras are basic,
       easy to get around.

03:34.415 --> 03:35.880
           This is it.

03:35.882 --> 03:37.882
  Craig: Looks like
a stack of poker chips.

03:37.884 --> 03:40.552
        $5 million stack
         of poker chips.

03:40.554 --> 03:41.754
A lot of foot traffic,
      as well.

03:41.756 --> 03:43.288
          Not at night.

03:43.290 --> 03:44.356
                   Deran:
        Steel bollards out front

03:44.358 --> 03:46.424
              so you can't bust
              a truck in here.

03:46.426 --> 03:47.359
     How'd they
     get it in?

03:47.361 --> 03:49.294
        Bollards retract.

03:49.296 --> 03:51.630
               Eh, if you have
                 a passcode.

03:51.632 --> 03:53.698
And the security guards
are a joke, but they can call

03:53.700 --> 03:57.369
the cops, who could be here
in less than two minutes.

03:57.371 --> 04:00.705
   -How much does this weigh?
            -3 tons.

04:00.707 --> 04:04.309
      So, basically, you want to
         break in here at night,

04:04.311 --> 04:05.978
                 get around
               the passcodes,

04:05.980 --> 04:07.780
        subdue the guards before
           they call the police,

04:07.782 --> 04:09.914
            get a truck in here,
                  somehow,

04:09.916 --> 04:12.985
        and get this 3-ton thing
         onto it, and get out --

04:12.987 --> 04:18.190
          oh, and don't drop it,
       because it's a art piece.

04:18.192 --> 04:19.791
     How would Smurf do it?

04:19.793 --> 04:22.927
       Uh, Smurf wouldn't do it.

04:22.929 --> 04:24.463
   I'm gonna check
    the cameras.

04:29.136 --> 04:31.403
                   Craig:
         The payout's sick, man.

04:31.405 --> 04:34.138
Yeah, I'm sure it is,
   but, I mean...

04:34.140 --> 04:38.543
We've got to figure out
how to do this shit first.

04:38.545 --> 04:40.078
    How about J?

04:40.080 --> 04:42.614
                J's on board
            if we say it's good.

04:42.616 --> 04:45.350
     The hell is
 that kid right now?

04:45.352 --> 04:48.953
               Doing something
                 for Smurf.

04:48.955 --> 04:51.156
    You're young.
You've invested well --

04:51.158 --> 04:53.291
    real estate,
  small businesses.

04:53.293 --> 04:55.960
       Yes. My grandmother died,
     and she left me some money.

04:55.962 --> 04:57.896
   Well, you're in
the right place, then.

04:57.898 --> 05:00.499
       I'm definitely interested
            in various shelters,

05:00.501 --> 05:02.501
              you know, for --
               for businesses.

05:02.503 --> 05:04.169
 Well, no one likes
      the IRS.

05:04.171 --> 05:06.839
  We specialize in
offshore holdings, trusts.

05:06.841 --> 05:09.107
 You just have to do
the paperwork correctly.

05:09.109 --> 05:11.910
                 And is your
               firm discreet?

05:11.912 --> 05:13.245
     Of course.

05:13.247 --> 05:17.182
What if I was looking for
a little extra discretion?

05:17.184 --> 05:18.650
                I'm not sure
               what you mean.

05:18.652 --> 05:20.719
          Receptionist:
      Thank you for calling
    Reinhorn and Associates.

05:20.721 --> 05:22.587
       How may I help you?

05:22.589 --> 05:23.756
         Yes, of course.

05:29.463 --> 05:31.263
              How did you hear
               about our firm?

05:31.265 --> 05:34.132
I know that you did work
 for Ronnie Ortega.

05:34.134 --> 05:38.537
I would be seeking a similar
type of representation.

05:38.539 --> 05:41.473
                Ronnie Ortega
          is no longer a client.

05:41.475 --> 05:44.543
                  He almost
              got me disbarred.

05:44.545 --> 05:47.546
           I do trusts and LLCs.

05:47.548 --> 05:49.614
                 That's it.

05:49.616 --> 05:53.418
Piece of advice, kid --

05:53.420 --> 05:54.820
         Pay your taxes.

05:57.157 --> 05:58.390
Thanks for your time.

06:08.769 --> 06:10.168
       Angela:
    Smells good.

06:10.170 --> 06:11.136
  Can I have some?

06:15.175 --> 06:16.175
        What time is it?

06:18.245 --> 06:21.045
              Pope:
           It's late.

06:21.047 --> 06:22.180
 I have a hard time
   falling asleep

06:22.182 --> 06:24.583
when I'm the only one
    in the room.

06:24.585 --> 06:25.851
   Only good thing
    about prison.

06:28.923 --> 06:30.655
   You still have
    those vases.

06:30.657 --> 06:32.524
        Those were there
        when I was a kid.

06:32.526 --> 06:35.928
           There was a
       fourth one, right?

06:35.930 --> 06:37.129
    I don't know.

06:37.131 --> 06:38.196
              Yeah.

06:38.198 --> 06:39.998
    Julia threw the last one
            at Smurf.

06:40.000 --> 06:41.533
           I was here.

06:41.535 --> 06:43.135
    Smurf didn't even flinch.

06:43.137 --> 06:44.803
        Those shards were
    on the floor all weekend,

06:44.805 --> 06:46.805
       till Julia finally
        cleaned them up.

06:46.807 --> 06:47.806
            Remember?

06:50.144 --> 06:52.344
Why do you still live here?

06:52.346 --> 06:53.912
              To save on rent.

06:56.216 --> 06:58.416
    Isn't it hard
 being around Smurf?

06:58.418 --> 06:59.551
                  I manage.

06:59.553 --> 07:01.019
      Oh, yeah?

07:01.021 --> 07:02.221
  That's managing?

07:04.358 --> 07:06.158
                    Here.

07:06.160 --> 07:08.293
       Oh, no.
I have to control my fats --

07:08.295 --> 07:11.163
  anything I can do
  to help my liver.

07:11.165 --> 07:14.432
After I got clean, my blood
tested positive for hep-C.

07:14.434 --> 07:15.567
         Dirty needles.

07:15.569 --> 07:17.035
   Yeah, probably.

07:17.037 --> 07:21.640
But it was acute, not chronic,
  so it's all good.

07:21.642 --> 07:24.242
     Where's J?
I thought he lived here.

07:24.244 --> 07:26.845
                   Oh, J,
             he comes and goes.

07:30.851 --> 07:32.116
             Thanks.

07:32.118 --> 07:34.586
      Last time I saw him,

07:34.588 --> 07:38.991
   right before Julia died...

07:38.993 --> 07:40.793
       it was getting bad.

07:40.795 --> 07:45.130
  You know, I told Julia that J
 needed to be somewhere stable,

07:45.132 --> 07:47.466
        somewhere clean.

07:47.468 --> 07:51.437
       She hit me so hard
I couldn't hear right for weeks.

07:54.541 --> 07:56.208
     That was the last time
           I saw her.

08:05.085 --> 08:06.551
              Well,
      thanks for breakfast.

08:06.553 --> 08:08.887
       Um, I've got to go.

08:08.889 --> 08:11.957
 My PO's on my ass. Says I have
 to get a job, like, yesterday.

08:16.230 --> 08:18.230
    Look at us...

08:18.232 --> 08:19.231
   together again.

08:21.902 --> 08:27.506
                     ♪♪

08:27.508 --> 08:33.111
                     ♪♪

08:33.113 --> 08:34.312
          Here, let me help you.

08:34.313 --> 08:35.514
        Smurf: I'm fine.

08:35.515 --> 08:43.121
                     ♪♪

08:43.123 --> 08:50.729
                     ♪♪

08:50.731 --> 08:52.597
      What are you seeing?

08:52.599 --> 08:57.269
  The doctor will review it, and
call you to go over the results.

08:57.271 --> 08:59.872
     You do this
   10 times a day.

08:59.874 --> 09:02.340
Why don't you just tell me
what you're looking at, there?

09:02.342 --> 09:04.409
                 The doctor
               will call you.

09:04.411 --> 09:11.016
                     ♪♪

09:14.621 --> 09:17.422
        ♪ Kalico Kahlia,
         come tell me ♪

09:17.424 --> 09:24.229
  ♪ The news Calamity's waiting
    for a way to get to her ♪

09:24.231 --> 09:26.699
                 I've got to
                take a piss.

09:26.701 --> 09:28.633
        Okay.
     Thank you.

09:28.635 --> 09:29.768
                   Mm-hmm.

09:36.510 --> 09:39.445
     [ Indistinct talking ]

09:43.650 --> 09:45.751
   I didn't know I
meant that much to you.

09:48.255 --> 09:50.789
              What?

09:50.791 --> 09:54.459
You're moping around
like someone kicked your dog.

09:54.461 --> 09:56.295
    You've got a high opinion
          of yourself.

09:59.666 --> 10:02.935
If you don't give a shit, then
stop staring at me like that.

10:02.937 --> 10:04.869
          We had a good
         thing going --

10:04.871 --> 10:08.673
         not me and you,
            the crew.

10:08.675 --> 10:11.676
      And I messed that up,
  and I'm just sorry about it.

10:11.678 --> 10:15.480
              Messed it up how,
             by bringing me in?

10:15.482 --> 10:17.282
             You're an asshole.
           You know that, right?

10:17.284 --> 10:19.417
        Oh, you're tough,
            now, huh?

10:19.419 --> 10:21.686
          You can hang
         with the guys.

10:21.688 --> 10:23.422
      You can handle this,
           handle him.

10:23.424 --> 10:27.692
      How about I worry about me
        and you worry about you?

10:27.694 --> 10:28.727
                    Yep.

10:32.833 --> 10:37.702
     You think he's some kind of
         war hero, or something.

10:37.704 --> 10:39.237
              I was there, too.

10:39.239 --> 10:41.039
           There were no heroes.

10:41.041 --> 10:44.977
         There were regular guys
             trying not to die,

10:44.979 --> 10:47.579
             and there were guys
            who got off on it --

10:47.581 --> 10:52.384
     guys who did that dark shit
      you have nightmares about.

10:52.386 --> 10:54.719
          Someone stole
        your girl, Jake.

10:54.721 --> 10:57.189
          Deal with it.
        Yeah, it's fine with me.

10:57.191 --> 10:58.390
               You're his now.

10:58.392 --> 11:00.192
              Hey.

11:00.194 --> 11:03.128
         I don't belong
           to anybody.

11:03.130 --> 11:04.263
               No, you didn't.

11:06.000 --> 11:07.199
               But you do now.

11:09.136 --> 11:13.005
                  Don't say
             I didn't warn you.

11:13.007 --> 11:18.043
  [ Indistinct talking, music ]

11:23.217 --> 11:25.617
         So, this guard's got me
              like this, dawg.

11:25.619 --> 11:27.486
               And he's like,
        "Where's the contraband?

11:27.488 --> 11:28.620
        Where's the contraband?"

11:28.622 --> 11:31.289
          And I'm like,
  "I ain't got no contraband."

11:31.291 --> 11:33.158
        Nah, I think you
         had contraband.

11:33.160 --> 11:34.893
       I'm saying, "No, no, no."

11:34.895 --> 11:36.761
      And all of a sudden,
              bam!

11:36.763 --> 11:38.230
               This explosion
          from behind my toilet.

11:38.232 --> 11:40.098
      Please don't tell me
     it was the raisin wine.

11:40.100 --> 11:43.368
         I put raisins and sugar
    in this 2-liter soda bottle,

11:43.370 --> 11:45.637
     and I forgot about it,
              dawg.

11:45.639 --> 11:47.840
       Right at the exact moment
           he's busting me up --

11:47.842 --> 11:49.174
             Kaboom!

11:49.176 --> 11:52.845
The whole D block smelled
 like Glade PlugIns.

11:52.847 --> 11:55.113
          Put my ass in solitary
               for two weeks.

11:55.115 --> 11:57.649
           [ Laughs ]

11:57.651 --> 11:59.384
    Man, I'm glad you're out.

11:59.386 --> 12:00.386
    Aren't you glad he's out?

12:02.256 --> 12:03.389
       Mm-hmm.

12:06.460 --> 12:07.660
          So, we gonna
        make some money?

12:10.931 --> 12:13.866
     I know some corner boys
       expecting a re-up.

12:16.002 --> 12:18.803
        Maybe we pay them
      a little visit, hmm?

12:18.805 --> 12:22.140
        Five large, easy.

12:22.142 --> 12:24.476
 Old times, brother.

12:24.478 --> 12:26.545
           Old times.

12:26.547 --> 12:28.613
Ah, I need a refill.

12:28.615 --> 12:36.088
                     ♪♪

12:36.090 --> 12:38.290
    It's nice to
   see you again.

12:38.292 --> 12:45.564
                     ♪♪

12:45.566 --> 12:47.031
       I thought about you
        while I was away.

12:47.033 --> 12:48.500
     Did you think about me?

12:48.502 --> 12:51.236
                     No.

12:51.238 --> 12:52.905
        Maybe me and you
     could be friends again.

12:52.907 --> 12:55.574
            I'm too old for you.

12:55.576 --> 13:03.448
                     ♪♪

13:03.450 --> 13:04.583
      Tupi: Oh,
  you rolling out?

13:04.585 --> 13:06.251
         I've got to mow
        my abuela's lawn.

13:06.253 --> 13:08.653
    It's looking all scraggly
     and weedy and whatnot.

13:08.655 --> 13:10.054
   All right, bro.

13:10.056 --> 13:11.023
   We'll hook up.

13:12.993 --> 13:14.993
      Craig: For starters,
       we need a forklift.

13:14.995 --> 13:17.062
  And then, we need to wrap up
  the forks in rubber bumpers.

13:17.064 --> 13:18.263
There's not enough time.

13:18.265 --> 13:19.998
 The cops are gonna
be there in minutes.

13:20.000 --> 13:22.401
         Well, then, we act like
     we're supposed to be there,

13:22.403 --> 13:23.936
          dress like art movers.

13:23.938 --> 13:26.871
    "Art movers?"
     Great idea.

13:26.873 --> 13:30.208
Then, we can get a helicopter
to come in and airlift it out.

13:30.210 --> 13:32.444
     These are just problems
          to be solved.

13:35.282 --> 13:37.682
        Yeah.

13:37.684 --> 13:40.552
       So, we have to lift
        something heavy.

13:40.554 --> 13:44.423
         What about, uh,
  a car lift from an auto shop?

13:44.425 --> 13:47.225
      You must know people
        in construction.

13:47.227 --> 13:48.293
         No.
 Smurf handles that.

13:48.295 --> 13:49.962
          But you know
         Smurf's people.

13:55.102 --> 13:56.635
        What about Pope?
          -Pope's out.

13:56.637 --> 13:57.836
              Why?

13:57.838 --> 13:59.204
     Pope's just
 not doing this one.

14:02.977 --> 14:04.709
                    Okay.

14:04.711 --> 14:06.244
                    Well,
          I have an appointment.

14:06.246 --> 14:08.847
          I'll meet up
         with you later.

14:08.849 --> 14:09.748
                   Craig:
             I'll walk you out.

14:16.923 --> 14:19.257
 I don't see how to
 make this job work.

14:19.259 --> 14:21.193
            It's big,
           it's slow,

14:21.195 --> 14:23.796
       And we're all about speed
                and surprise.

14:23.798 --> 14:25.464
   It's not a job.

14:25.466 --> 14:29.334
  It's a puzzle --
  man versus rock,

14:29.336 --> 14:31.470
    the Egyptians
building the pyramids.

14:31.472 --> 14:33.672
              Yeah, but didn't
              they have slaves?

14:33.674 --> 14:35.940
I didn't bring this job
    to the Codys.

14:35.942 --> 14:38.276
I brought it to you.

14:38.278 --> 14:39.345
   Figure it out.

14:44.819 --> 14:48.687
         Yo, when did the health
      department give you a "B?"

14:48.689 --> 14:50.288
Deran: It's a bar, man,
  not a restaurant.

14:50.290 --> 14:53.091
People don't come here
    for the food.

14:53.093 --> 14:55.360
Look, if you really want to
get this thing on a truck

14:55.362 --> 14:58.963
without it getting scratched or
ruined or anything like that...

14:58.965 --> 15:02.701
You have a wide load going
40 to 50 miles per hour, tops.

15:02.703 --> 15:04.236
    Just saying.

15:04.238 --> 15:06.038
        You're thinking about it
             the wrong way, man.

15:06.040 --> 15:07.772
               It's -- It's...

15:07.774 --> 15:08.773
               It's not a job.

15:08.775 --> 15:09.908
              It's -- It's a...

15:09.910 --> 15:11.844
               It's a puzzle.

15:11.846 --> 15:13.378
  Puzzle?
                       Mm-hmm.

15:13.380 --> 15:16.981
              Man versus rock.

15:16.983 --> 15:18.050
 "Man versus rock?"

15:18.052 --> 15:20.118
        Okay.

15:20.120 --> 15:22.120
Look, how well do you
  know this girl --

15:22.122 --> 15:23.255
I mean, actually know
     this girl?

15:23.257 --> 15:25.057
                        Frankie?
      Yeah.

15:25.059 --> 15:26.258
           Don't worry about it.

15:26.260 --> 15:28.393
"Don't worry about it."
     All right.

15:28.395 --> 15:30.195
  What about Pope?

15:30.197 --> 15:31.463
                   No way.

15:31.465 --> 15:33.798
   He's gonna be pissed off if
 he finds out we're doing this.

15:33.800 --> 15:36.801
            So, what? We just --
        We just bring him along,

15:36.803 --> 15:39.538
      hope he doesn't act crazy,
     try another suicide by cop?

15:39.540 --> 15:40.605
 Hey, we don't know
      if that's

15:40.607 --> 15:41.940
what he was actually
    trying to do.

15:41.942 --> 15:44.609
         You weren't there, man.

15:44.611 --> 15:46.811
       He tried to kill himself,
                 all right?

15:46.813 --> 15:47.780
                  I saw it.

15:50.751 --> 15:52.284
We just have to keep him
  away from Smurf.

