35:08.875 --> 35:13.478
    Jesus Christ, you really are
 a Goddamn shell-shocked psycho.

35:13.480 --> 35:14.746
I should've iced you
    in the bank.

35:14.748 --> 35:15.681
           [ Gunshot ]

35:17.952 --> 35:24.689
                     ♪♪

35:24.691 --> 35:31.363
                     ♪♪

35:31.365 --> 35:33.098
        [ Sighs heavily ]

35:33.100 --> 35:34.199
              Damn.

35:35.369 --> 35:37.770
        See?

35:37.772 --> 35:39.138
You do want to live.

35:41.776 --> 35:43.642
Get serious, Janine.

35:43.644 --> 35:50.783
                     ♪♪

35:50.785 --> 35:52.517
            [ Sighs ]

35:52.519 --> 36:00.392
                     ♪♪

36:00.394 --> 36:08.266
                     ♪♪

36:08.268 --> 36:11.403
               She's as crazy
                  as he is.

36:11.405 --> 36:12.571
     True love.

36:25.418 --> 36:26.352
                I got a job.

36:29.356 --> 36:30.555
     Pope: Yeah?

36:30.557 --> 36:31.724
                    Yeah.

36:34.695 --> 36:37.162
       Where?

36:37.164 --> 36:39.030
                 101 Diner.

36:39.032 --> 36:42.267
   Dishwasher, but I can move up
to waitress if I show up steady.

36:45.172 --> 36:47.172
        When?

36:47.174 --> 36:48.207
                Couple hours.

36:51.178 --> 36:53.378
     You should
   get some sleep.

36:53.380 --> 36:55.080
                 That's what
            coffee's for, right?

37:03.857 --> 37:05.391
                 Hey, um...

37:09.262 --> 37:10.162
              ...I lied to you.

37:13.066 --> 37:14.333
                    I...

37:14.335 --> 37:15.701
             I ripped Julia off.

37:17.804 --> 37:20.139
                  And then,
             I ran out on her --

37:20.141 --> 37:21.140
                   and J.

37:24.211 --> 37:25.911
               I've been lying
               my whole life.

37:28.281 --> 37:30.215
                 It's easier
               than the truth.

37:30.217 --> 37:32.217
                   But...

37:32.219 --> 37:33.752
                I'm trying to
              be better, so...

37:36.223 --> 37:39.024
    Do you think
 people can change?

37:41.162 --> 37:43.762
                    Yeah.

37:43.764 --> 37:45.831
                    I do.

37:45.833 --> 37:48.367
              My life is better
               when I'm clean.

37:48.369 --> 37:51.302
               It's less fun,
                   but...

37:51.304 --> 37:52.371
                 less scary.

37:52.373 --> 37:59.378
                     ♪♪

37:59.380 --> 38:02.781
          You never really liked
             getting high, huh?

38:02.783 --> 38:03.816
       Well...

38:07.254 --> 38:09.320
 ...drugs don't work
       on me.

38:09.322 --> 38:14.593
                     ♪♪

38:14.595 --> 38:20.065
                     ♪♪

38:20.067 --> 38:21.233
      Frankie:
Where have you been?

38:27.274 --> 38:28.607
  What did you do?

38:28.609 --> 38:31.210
     Broke in the building,
      tagged the sculpture,

38:31.212 --> 38:33.344
         and pretty much
        everything else.

38:33.346 --> 38:35.414
You did what?
             Relax.

38:35.416 --> 38:37.416
        It's spray chalk.

38:37.418 --> 38:39.151
       You can wash it off
          with a hose.

38:42.223 --> 38:45.690
              Darrell Stone --
      total trust-fund douchebag

38:45.692 --> 38:47.492
           who bought a Ferrari.

38:47.494 --> 38:49.494
   He would drive it around town
 at, like, 100 miles per hour --

38:49.496 --> 38:52.231
               and I'm talking
      residential neighborhoods.

38:52.233 --> 38:55.434
               Until, one day,
         he swipes a phone pole.

38:55.436 --> 38:57.836
                Cost him 20K
              to get it fixed.

38:57.838 --> 39:01.973
        After that, dude kept it
               in the garage.

39:01.975 --> 39:04.109
    What are you
   talking about?

39:04.111 --> 39:07.846
        See, these rich dudes --
           they're all the same.

39:07.848 --> 39:11.116
          They go around flexing
         until there's a hiccup,

39:11.118 --> 39:12.718
                  and then,
             their balls shrink.

39:12.720 --> 39:14.853
So, when that guy who owns
the sculpture finds out

39:14.855 --> 39:17.388
that someone's tagged it,
he's gonna get it out of there,

39:17.390 --> 39:20.259
and put it someplace safe --
     guaranteed.

39:20.261 --> 39:21.526
   And to move it,

39:21.528 --> 39:22.994
they've got to put it
     on a truck.

39:22.996 --> 39:25.664
And once that truck's
   on the street,

39:25.666 --> 39:27.799
that's when we hit it.

39:27.801 --> 39:30.335
    You asked me
  to figure it out.

39:30.337 --> 39:31.870
     This is me
  figuring it out.

39:33.407 --> 39:36.074
  Pete: Why don't you throw in
      the '64 Impala, huh?

39:36.076 --> 39:37.342
        Tina: No problem.

39:37.344 --> 39:39.678
         It's my mom's.

39:39.680 --> 39:41.880
  Yo, what the hell
      is this?!

39:41.882 --> 39:44.483
Lencho's dead, and you're just
sitting here playing cards?!

39:44.485 --> 39:46.217
         Hey, guillado.

39:46.219 --> 39:47.886
          You're drunk.

39:47.888 --> 39:50.555
We've got to go find out who did
this, and go make it right!

39:50.557 --> 39:54.225
 Lencho was robbing corner boys,
             que no?

39:54.227 --> 39:56.295
You'd do me like that?

39:56.297 --> 39:58.897
      If you did something
          that stupid.

39:58.899 --> 40:00.499
Hey, I got it.

40:00.501 --> 40:01.433
Muévete.

40:04.638 --> 40:06.638
  You can't run up
 on Pete like that.

40:06.640 --> 40:09.108
Nobody's talking on the streets
yet, but I'll find out --

40:09.110 --> 40:10.909
                    Okay.

40:10.911 --> 40:12.577
Why are you so calm?

40:12.579 --> 40:13.512
You were his girlfriend
    that summer.

40:13.514 --> 40:15.647
            The summer I was 12?

40:15.649 --> 40:16.781
   He was family.

40:16.783 --> 40:19.418
                Your family,
                  not mine.

40:24.391 --> 40:26.858
                    What?

40:26.860 --> 40:29.461
            You think I did him?

40:29.463 --> 40:32.597
      Yeah, I hated the pendejo,
                  but then,

40:32.599 --> 40:35.400
             so did 100 dipshits
               all over town.

40:35.402 --> 40:38.337
          They were just waiting
          for Lencho to get out.

40:38.339 --> 40:39.938
 Then, we've got to
  hit them back --

40:39.940 --> 40:41.473
     you and me.

40:41.475 --> 40:44.275
                  Go home.

40:44.277 --> 40:46.411
     "Go home"?!

40:46.413 --> 40:48.947
You know I got collectors
knocking on my door.

40:48.949 --> 40:52.217
So, if Lencho's not around,
it's just you and me.

40:52.219 --> 40:53.885
 And we're gonna hit
    that mark-ass

40:53.887 --> 40:55.887
   white boyfriend
      of yours.

40:55.889 --> 41:02.094
                     ♪♪

41:05.966 --> 41:14.840
                     ♪♪

41:14.842 --> 41:23.582
                     ♪♪

41:23.584 --> 41:32.257
                     ♪♪

41:32.259 --> 41:40.999
                     ♪♪

41:41.001 --> 41:49.775
                     ♪♪

41:55.816 --> 41:57.616
       He's having the sculpture
            moved on Saturday --

41:57.618 --> 42:00.786
   doesn't feel like his artwork
is safe in the building anymore.

42:02.823 --> 42:04.423
         You're not gonna gloat,
                  are you?

42:04.425 --> 42:05.724
  Am I gonna gloat?

42:07.628 --> 42:09.194
     Hell yeah,
  I'm gonna gloat.

42:14.568 --> 42:15.834
               J:
    I found your new lawyer.

42:15.836 --> 42:17.036
             Smurf:
     I don't need a lawyer.

42:17.038 --> 42:19.705
    I already have a lawyer.

42:19.707 --> 42:23.909
You didn't think I was gonna sit
around and wait for you, do you?

42:23.911 --> 42:24.910
       Hey, J?

42:27.380 --> 42:30.515
 You see Angela yet?

42:30.517 --> 42:32.451
        Hmm?

42:32.453 --> 42:36.722
You two used to be mighty close
when your mom was alive.

42:36.724 --> 42:39.658
 Maybe you should do
a little catching up.

42:39.660 --> 42:44.529
                     ♪♪

42:44.531 --> 42:47.066
   Craig: Mimosa?

42:47.068 --> 42:48.467
                What is this,
              a bridal shower?

42:51.872 --> 42:54.005
                    Hey,
             look who showed up.

42:54.007 --> 42:55.540
             You have a nice day
       running errands for Smurf

42:55.542 --> 42:58.143
              while we've been
         working this thing out?

42:58.145 --> 42:59.544
       Job's on Saturday.

42:59.546 --> 43:00.946
           -Saturday?
            -Uh-huh.

43:00.948 --> 43:02.414
         They're moving
         the sculpture.

43:02.416 --> 43:05.484
 We already know the route, and
  we're gonna hijack the truck.

43:05.486 --> 43:06.485
         Well, what kind
         of truck is it?

43:06.487 --> 43:08.353
     Flatbed --
     slow, easy.

43:08.355 --> 43:09.955
                Why are they
                 moving it?

43:09.957 --> 43:12.223
Because I'm brilliant.

43:12.225 --> 43:13.825
         What's the pay?

43:13.827 --> 43:16.161
     800 grand.

43:16.163 --> 43:17.663
                 For a hunk
                of concrete.

43:22.503 --> 43:24.770
               He'll be fine.

43:24.772 --> 43:28.507
 But if he finds out we're doing
       this thing without him...

43:28.509 --> 43:30.442
     Yeah, okay.

43:30.444 --> 43:32.911
                 Hey, Pope.

43:32.913 --> 43:34.580
             Can we talk to you
                for a second?

43:41.454 --> 43:43.389
      [ Cellphone buzzes ]

43:45.659 --> 43:48.393
      [ Buzzing continues ]

43:48.395 --> 43:49.328
        [ Buzzing stops]

43:52.265 --> 43:53.999
      Good morning, Doctor.

43:54.001 --> 43:55.066
                   Doctor:
      <i> Uh, good morning, Janine.</i>
       <i> I need you to come in --</i>

43:55.068 --> 43:57.669
               No.
      I won't be coming in.

43:57.671 --> 43:59.471
          <i> -Well, uh --</i>
         -Just tell me.

43:59.473 --> 44:01.807
             <i> I'm sorry, Janine,</i>
          <i> but your test results</i>

44:01.809 --> 44:04.343
             <i> came back positive</i>
               <i> for melanoma.</i>

44:04.345 --> 44:06.345
                  <i> You have</i>
                <i> skin cancer.</i>

44:06.347 --> 44:08.680
         <i> And it's spread to the</i>
        <i> lymph nodes, uh, bones,</i>

44:08.682 --> 44:10.615
              <i> and your liver,</i>
                  <i> as well.</i>

44:10.617 --> 44:12.417
        <i> Now, there are a number</i>
          <i> of treatment options.</i>

44:12.419 --> 44:15.020
           <i> We should start with</i>
       <i> chemotherapy right away.</i>

